Merloc <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zurrenal>Zurren AL</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 605<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/10/03 9:59 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> Old news, and its more or less weaponshiled that allowed them to pull it off.. and really, I dont care one damn bit, 4 of the 6 of them were dead by time they won (but probably with pratice, they could lower that number).<br>
<br>
They are also geared/AA'd out the ass, and it took them longer then a couple of seconds to do it.<br>
<br>
And, the primary reason for nerfing MB (while dragon farming was one, but not the only) was to prevent lower end PoP content from becomming trivialized. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=istari@graffeswizardcompilation>Istari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 350<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/10/03 10:02 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> I do more than 9.6k to any pop boss fight, even crap minibosses from the HP ring. Probably only the REAL low hp pop mobs such as MB would be trivialized, and even then they're not tough fights. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=quineloe>Quineloe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1852<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/10/03 10:53 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> Stuff like Carprin - Highpriest cycle would have been totally trivialized by manaburn. <p>Sage Quineloe<br>
